msContents.summary: Copy of Saʻdī's Gulistān, missing the last leaf.

supportDesc.extent: 225 numbered pages : 202 x 131 (155 x 88) mm, bound to 206 x 137 x 22 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 15 lines in long lines and two columns.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Polychrome and gold headpiece (f. 1v), textblock border-ruled in gold and blue; rubricatons in red; columns and some lines ruled in gold.

binding.p: Bound in plain black leather with blind ruled frame.

origin.p: Item is undated, probably produced in the 17th or 18th century.

history.provenance: Given by Mrs. A. V. W. Jackson in December 1937 (library plate, inside front cover).
Gift from A. Beijan to A. V. W. Jackson in 1921 (inscription, flyleaf 1 recto at front of book).
